quiz.name: Post Assessment
quiz.intro:
Hello folks,

Please take this post assessment quiz to complete the Self Awareness course.

Warmly,

Team Llama

feedback.feedbacktext: Well done, you’re very self-aware!
You’re mostly self-aware, with a few areas you can develop.
You have some self-awareness, but there’s definitely room for improvement.
You’re lacking self-awareness... but you can learn!

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name the behaviours that you are doing at all times?
: Yes, I’m always intentional with my behaviors and can name what I’m taking part
in at all times. ; Sometimes. I’m usually aware of what I’m doing, although at times, I get caught
up in something or don’t realize what I’m doing. ; No, I rarely am aware of what my body or mind is doing.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I’m always intentional with my behaviors and can name what I’m taking part
in at all times.
question_attempt.responsesummary:
Sometimes. I’m usually aware of what I’m doing, although at times, I get caught
up in something or don’t realize what I’m doing.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you state a list of goals and ambitions you have for yourself?
: Somewhat. I have a few goals and ambitions, although they might not be the most
defined. ; No, I don’t really have any driving goals or ambitions in my life.
; Yes, I can state a list of goals right now that include both short-term and long-term
goals. I understand what I want out of life and can express these ambitions.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can state a list of goals right now that include both short-term and long-term
goals. I understand what I want out of life and can express these ambitions.
question_attempt.responsesummary:
Yes, I can state a list of goals right now that include both short-term and long-term
goals. I understand what I want out of life and can express these ambitions.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you describe the environment you thrive in the most?
: No, I don’t know what environment works best for me. I just try to make it work
; Yes, I can describe the ideal environment that I need to be happy and be
successful, including the pace, energy, and structure that I thrive in. ; Somewhat. I know certain things that I would want, but I can’t fully describe the
exact environment that I thrive in.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can describe the ideal environment that I need to be happy and be
successful, including the pace, energy, and structure that I thrive in.
question_attempt.responsesummary: No, I don’t know what environment works best for me. I just try to make it work

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you identify a list of personal strengths and how they manifest themselves in your life? : No, I don’t know what my strengths are. I just try to do my best.
; Yes, I can list all of my strengths right now, as well as where they fit into my life
and how I use them to find success. ; Somewhat. I mostly know what I’m good at, although I couldn’t tell you exactly
how I incorporate these strengths into my life.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can list all of my strengths right now, as well as where they fit into my life
and how I use them to find success.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you identify a list of shortcomings and how they manifest themselves in your life? : Somewhat. I mostly know what my weaknesses are, although I don’t have an
exact list. I try to avoid them, but I don’t really know how they hold me back. ; No, I don’t know what my shortcomings are.
; Yes, I can list all of my shortcomings right now, as well as how they affect my life
and what I need to do to overcome them.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can list all of my shortcomings right now, as well as how they affect my life
and what I need to do to overcome them.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you describe your typical reaction to new information, whether it be positive or negative?
: No, I just react in the moment and don’t know of any patterns.
; Yes, I can tell you right now how I usually react to new information. I understand my natural tendencies with both what emotions I feel and what impulses I have.
; Somewhat. I can generally describe how I react to positive and negative news, but I’m not fully aware of my emotions and thoughts.
question_attempt.rightanswer: Yes, I can tell you right now how I usually react to new information. I understand my natural tendencies with both what emotions I feel and what impulses I have.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name what you need in your relationships to feel fulfilled?
: No, I don’t know what I need from my relationships to feel fulfilled.
; Yes, I can name exactly what I need in my life in my relationships to create a sense of belonging and feel fulfilled. Additionally, I’m able to express these needs.
; Somewhat. I know what I need from others, although I might not know specifically what I need from each person or in different situations.
question_attempt.rightanswer: Yes, I can name exactly what I need in my life in my relationships to create a sense of belonging and feel fulfilled. Additionally, I’m able to express these needs.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you list the relationships in your life and which ones meet your needs?
: Somewhat. I can list the people that are in my life, as well as my most important relationships, but my connections aren’t always perfect.; Yes, I can list the relationships I have in my life right now and evaluate what they give me. I know what I need to feel a strong connection.
; No, I don’t give much thought to the people in my life and which relationships meet my needs.
question_attempt.rightanswer: Yes, I can list the relationships I have in my life right now and evaluate what they give me. I know what I need to feel a strong connection.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you accurately describe the impact you have on others?
: b) Somewhat. I know what impact I have on others in general, although I couldn’t get into the specifics.
; a) Yes, I know the impact I have on others, including what they think of me, how my words and actions affect them, and what my role is in their life.
; c) No, I don’t know how my words and actions affect others.
question_attempt.rightanswer: a) Yes, I know the impact I have on others, including what they think of me, how my words and actions affect them, and what my role is in their life.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you identify where in your life biases and natural human tendencies play a role in your thinking?
: c) No, I have no idea about natural human tendencies or how they get in the way of self-awareness.
; a) Yes, I’m aware of where my thoughts and actions are influenced by biases and natural human tendencies. I can identify and name when these factors are getting in the way of my self-awareness and mindset.
; b) Sometimes. I understand that I’m influenced by human nature, but I don’t always know what these influences are or how they affect me.
question_attempt.rightanswer: a) Yes, I’m aware of where my thoughts and actions are influenced by biases and natural human tendencies. I can identify and name when these factors are getting in the way of my self-awareness and mindset.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name your primary coping mechanisms, and what triggers them?
: Sometimes. I know what coping mechanisms I generally use when trying to defend myself, but I can’t always recognize what triggers them.
; Yes, I can list my primary coping mechanisms right now and what situations trigger them. I understand how they developed in my past and can evaluate whether they still serve me now.
; No, I have no idea what coping mechanisms I default to or why.
question_attempt.rightanswer: Yes, I can list my primary coping mechanisms right now and what situations trigger them. I understand how they developed in my past and can evaluate whether they still serve me now.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name the emotions that you are feeling at all times?
: No, I rarely think about what emotion I’m feeling. I just feel something and act
accordingly. ; Sometimes. I’m usually aware of what emotion I’m feeling. However, it takes me a
few moments to recognize it, and strong emotions sometimes catch me off-guard. ; Yes, I can always identify and name the emotion I’m feeling at any given moment.
question_attempt.rightanswer: Yes, I can always identify and name the emotion I’m feeling at any given moment.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you evaluate how much of an impact cultural narratives have on you, and can you identify where they influence your thinking?
: Sometimes. I know that cultural narratives exist and can sometimes recognize where the influence my thinking. That being said, I imagine there are aspects of society that affect me that I don’t realize.
; Yes, I’m aware of the cultural narratives that exist and how they influence my thinking and perspective. I can distinguish between what I know to be true and what I feel like I should do, as told by society.
; No, I don’t know what “cultural narrative” means, let alone how it affects me.
question_attempt.rightanswer: Yes, I’m aware of the cultural narratives that exist and how they influence my thinking and perspective. I can distinguish between what I know to be true and what I feel like I should do, as told by society.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you identify what causes a shift to negative emotions?
: No, I rarely know what specifically causes me to shift to negative emotions. All of a
sudden, I’m no longer happy and I don’t know why. ; Yes, I can always identify what causes me to shift to negative emotions, whether it
be an event, person, or recurring trigger. ; Sometimes. I can usually identify what caused a shift in emotions, although it
takes a little while for me to catch on.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can always identify what causes me to shift to negative emotions, whether it
be an event, person, or recurring trigger.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name the emotional patterns you experience the most?
: No, I have no idea what emotional patterns I repeat. I have emotions, but I can’t
name any trends with when or why they happen. ; Somewhat. I generally know what I have a tendency to do, but it’s not always
consistent or recognizable. ; Yes, I can list my standard emotional patterns right now, including what they are,
what causes them, and what effect they have on my life.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I can list my standard emotional patterns right now, including what they are,
what causes them, and what effect they have on my life.

question_attempt.questionsummary:
Can you name your deepest fear triggers?
: No, I have no idea what a fear trigger even is or if I have one.
; Yes, I’m aware of my deepest fears and what triggers these fears in my everyday
life. I understand how pervasive these fears are in my thoughts and actions. ; Somewhat. I can tell you what I’m most scared of, but I don’t fully know how it
affects my life and daily actions.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I’m aware of my deepest fears and what triggers these fears in my everyday
life. I understand how pervasive these fears are in my thoughts and actions.

; Yes, I know the things that give me the most shame and what triggers this shame
in my everyday life. I understand how pervasive this shame is in my thoughts and
actions.
question_attempt.rightanswer:
Yes, I know the things that give me the most shame and what triggers this shame
in my everyday life. I understand how pervasive this shame is in my thoughts and
actions.

; Yes, I can list my guiding principles and core values right now. I know how to
distinguish between what I care about and the outside influence of others.

Yes, I can list my guiding principles and core values right now. I know how to
